But what you not consider here is that the only reason our pets kill a L45 mob is because, it dual wield we speed it with a 65% haste, very few mobs do this in game, only special mobs at that level dual wield.<br>
What will an enchanter do, he will give the chamed mobs weapons to enable its dual wield and he will add a haste buff, most likely Shissar that is 66% Haste. Then add the fact that Luclin have tons of undercon mobs. The end result is pure nasty, there are TONs of mobs he can charm that hit for 130+, have around 5-8k hp and with weapons and now will quad hit enchanter speeded. This pet easy have twice the dmg output compared to our epic and in many cases twice the hp.<br>
Also add to the fun that he can charm a shaman mob that will do all the slowing for him and even heal, get a wizard mob and suddenly he will have a mob that instead of our wizzy pet that nuke for 170pt will nuke for 600+ and will add a 11pt dmg shield to itself, or why not a necromancer pet or shadowknight pet that pet will snare mobs too, or maybe a cleric pet, those CH are nice.<br>
<br>
Then think one step further then you see 4 chanters grouped together runing around with 1 Cleric pet, 1 shaman pet, 2 warrior typ pets all that quad for 130, the chanter with cleric pet just stand back a bit and let his pet heal the melee and shammy pet.<br>
<br>
This skill is so powerfull that it is stupid even with refresh timer of 72mins.<br>
